# CodeMaps Diagram Editing

When the user asks to draw, update, split, or visualize a system architecture, edit `diagrams/current.json`.

## Rules

1. Always read `diagrams/current.json` before editing
2. Validate against `diagram.schema.json`
3. Use unique kebab-case IDs for nodes and edges
4. New nodes: omit `position` (auto-layout)
5. Do not change positions of existing nodes unless asked
6. Update `metadata.updatedAt` to current ISO timestamp on every save
7. Ensure all edge source/target reference valid node IDs

## Node types

`service` | `database` | `component` | `queue` | `cache` | `external` | `group`

## Edge types

`http` | `websocket` | `event` | `dependency` | `data-flow`

